ZIGGY Balayage is a efficient placement that would in alternating diagonal back and forward sections working up the headshape! 

I  suggest to only surface paint to allow depth to be left behind for a contrast result. 

I took about 2” sections consistently throughout the entire process. 

If you want more saturation of colour then choose 1” sections in between but it will be less contrasted! 

If you take 3” sections you will achieve more depth less light panels 

I want to unlock that curious colorist within your magical self!!!!
